The gluten-free products market can be segmented based on product type, distribution channel, and region. In terms of product type, the market includes a wide range of gluten-free products such as bakery items, baby food, pasta, ready meals, and other variants. The distribution channels for these products mainly consist of hypermarkets/supermarkets, convenience stores, specialty stores, and online retail platforms. Geographically, the market is divided into regions like North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa, each with its own consumption patterns and preferences for gluten-free products.

